The line where the TODO is located is inside the loop where we check if the distance to y is greater than the distance to x plus one. In BFS for unweighted graphs, when you find a shorter path to a node, you update its distance and add it to the queue. So, when dist[y] > dist[x] + 1, we should set dist[y] to dist[x] + 1 and then enqueue y. That's the standard BFS approach for shortest paths. Looking at the code, after the condition, the next step is to update the distance for y and push it into the queue. So the missing code should be:

dist[y] = dist[x] + 1;
q.push(y);

That makes sense.
